# [GAIA](../wg/gaia.html)

**IETF 125 Session Minutes**

## Summary
The Global Access to the Internet for All (GAIA) research group met at IETF 125 to discuss diverse aspects of global connectivity, ranging from hardware sustainability and community-led infrastructure to CDN ecosystems and infrastructure resilience. Key highlights included a discussion on adopting a draft for circular device management, a report on community fiber deployments in the Philippines, a global measurement study of Twitch’s CDN, the introduction of a financial planning tool for local networks, and an analysis of the interdependence between power grids and internet resilience.

## Key Discussion Points

### 1. Opening and WG Status
**Presenter:** Adisorn Lertsinsrubtavee
**Slides:** [Opening_GAIA_IETF125](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-gaia-opening-gaia-co-chair-01)

